        <h1>What is a balanced diet?</h1>
        <p>A balanced diet is a way of eating that includes all of the nutrients your body needs to function properly. These nutrients include carbohydrates, proteins, fats, vitamins, and minerals. A balanced diet is essential for overall health and wellness, and can help you maintain a healthy weight, have more energy, and reduce your risk of chronic diseases.</p>
        <p>But what does a balanced diet actually look like? Here are some tips to help you create a balanced diet:</p>
        <p>1. Include a variety of foods. A balanced diet includes a variety of different types of foods to ensure you're getting all the nutrients you need. This includes fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats.</p>
        <img src="images/blog-3-photo-1.jpg" alt="">
        <p>2. Eat the right amount of calories. The number of calories you need depends on your age, gender, weight, height, and physical activity level. It's important to find the right balance of calories to maintain a healthy weight.</p>
        <p>3. Choose nutrient-dense foods. Nutrient-dense foods are those that provide a lot of nutrients for relatively few calories. These include fruits, vegetables, and whole grains.</p>
        <img src="images/blog-3-photo-2.jpg" alt="">
        <p>4. Limit added sugars and unhealthy fats. Too much added sugar and unhealthy fats can contribute to weight gain and increase your risk of chronic diseases. Choose foods that are lower in these nutrients and opt for healthier options like unsaturated fats from sources like avocados, nuts, and olive oil.</p>
        <img src="images/blog-3-photo-3.jpg" alt="">
        <p>5. Don't forget to hydrate. Proper hydration is essential for overall health and can help you feel more energized and focused. Aim for at least 8-8 ounces of water each day.</p>
        <img src="images/blog-3-photo-4.jpg" alt="">
        <p>By following these tips, you can create a balanced diet that will help you feel your best. Just remember to listen to your body and be mindful of your individual needs and preferences.</p>
